<html>
<head>
    <!-- Bootstrap CSS -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap-icons/font/bootstrap-icons.css">
    <!-- Include jsPDF and html2canvas -->
    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/html2canvas/1.4.1/html2canvas.min.js"></script>
    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/jspdf/2.5.1/jspdf.umd.min.js"></script>

    <style>
        @@page {
            size: A4;
            margin: 20mm;
        }

        / Print styles /
        @@media print {
            body

        {
            background-color: #fff;
        }

        }

        body {
            font-family: 'Cambria Math';
            margin: 20px;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: #f8f9fa;
        }

        .container-box {
            max-width: 900px;
            background: white;
            border: 2px solid #000;
            padding: 20px;
            box-shadow: 5px 5px 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
        }

        .header-table {
            width: 100%;
            border-collapse: collapse;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

            .header-table td {
                border: 1px solid #000;
                padding: 8px;
                text-align: left;
            }



        h1 {
            font-size: 24px;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        h2 {
            font-size: 18px;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        .underline {
            text-decoration: underline;
        }

        td {
            border: 1px solid black;
            padding: 8px;
            text-align: left;
            vertical-align: middle;
        }


        th {
            text-align: center;
            border: 1px solid black;
            padding: 8px;
            vertical-align: middle;
            word-break: break-word;
            white-space: normal;
            overflow-wrap: break-word;
        }

        .company-title {
            font-size: 20px;
            font-weight: bold;
            letter-spacing: 1px;
            white-space: nowrap;
            word-spacing: 5px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <!-- Close Button -->
    <a asp-area="MST_Company" id="top-logo" asp-controller="MST_Company" asp-action="CompanyDetail" class="btn btn-link position-absolute top-0 end-0 m-3 text-dark">
        <i class="bi bi-x-lg fs-4"></i>
    </a>
    <button id="downloadPdf" class="btn btn-primary my-3">Download PDF</button>

    <div class="container my-5" id="pdf-content">
        <div class="container-box mx-auto p-4">
            <table class="header-table">
                <tr>
                    <td class="company-title" colspan="2">QUALITY MANUAL</td>
                    <td class="company-title" colspan="2">BLIZZARD CERAMICA LLP</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td colspan="2">SUBJECT : Table of contents</td>
                    <td>Edition No. : 01</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td colspan="2">Standard : ISO 9001 : 2015</td>
                    <td>Rev. No. & Date : 01 / 01.08.2024</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td colspan="3">Page No. : 20 of 79</td>
                </tr>
            </table>

            <div class="content">
                <p>
                    The top management must implement and promote a culture of risk-based
                    thinking throughout the organization to determine and address the risks
                    and opportunities associated with providing assurance that the QMS.
                    Address risk department and process wise and risk identified as process,
                    requirements, Failure mode, Define risk in the process, Consequences,
                    likelihood, Risk level, needed actions to improve process. Requirement
                    of the Risk identification to provide conforming products and services,
                    enhance customer satisfaction; promote desirable effects and improvement;
                    and prevent, or mitigate, undesired effects.
                </p>
                <p>
                    BCL has been evaluating these processes based on measurement and monitoring
                    records, and performance indicator of each process like Conformity of
                    product, customer satisfaction, performance and effectiveness of QMS,
                    Implementation of planning, effectiveness of action taken to address risk
                    and opportunities, Evaluation of external provider like supplier, These
                    reviews must identify opportunities to improve QMS processes, use of
                    resources and product quality.
                </p>
                <p>
                    BCL has look opportunities for improve for the process and for quality management system.
                </p>
                <h2>4.4.2 To the extent necessary, the BCL shall </h2>
                <p>
                    Documented information is carried out as per Interaction and sequences of processes.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Maintain documented information to support the operation of its processes. like Procedure,
                    Machine list, Critical Spare part list,  Measuring equipment list, Material Specification Chart.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Maintenance, Monitoring of machine Break down, Production planning and monitoring, Training,
                    Calibration of measuring equipment. Analysis of objective like delivery performance,
                    Non-conformity of product and processes, risk Identification and its Improvements.
                </p>
                <p class="company-title text-start">
                    Documented Information
                </p>
                <p class="company-title text-start ">
                    <strong>List of Process & Procedure	</strong>   : DMR07
                </p>
                <table class="header-table">
                    <tr>
                        <td style="width:35%; height:5vh;"></td>
                        <td style="width:35%; height:5vh;"></td>
                        <td rowspan="2"></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td class="text-center">Prepared By </td>
                        <td class="text-center">Approved By</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <script>
        document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", () => {
            document.getElementById("downloadPdf").addEventListener("click", () => {
                const { jsPDF } = window.jspdf;
                const pdf = new jsPDF("p", "mm", "a4");

                // Get elements to hide
                const btn = document.getElementById("downloadPdf");
                const logo = document.getElementById("top-logo");

                // Temporarily hide elements
                if (btn) btn.style.display = "none";
                if (logo) logo.style.display = "none";

                html2canvas(document.getElementById("pdf-content")).then(canvas => {
                    const imgData = canvas.toDataURL("image/png");
                    const imgWidth = 190; // A4 width in mm
                    const imgHeight = (canvas.height * imgWidth) / canvas.width;

                    pdf.addImage(imgData, "PNG", 10, 10, imgWidth, imgHeight);
                    pdf.save("QM_P20.pdf");

                    // Restore elements after PDF is generated
                    if (btn) btn.style.display = "block";
                    if (logo) logo.style.display = "block";
                });
            });
        });

    </script>
</body>
</html>